The right side is $M$ times the count of multiples of $p$ in one interval. The count is at most $\lceil (n - n/M)/p \rceil = \lceil (n(1 - 1/M))/p \rceil$. 

Since $p > \sqrt{n}$, we have $\lfloor n/p \rfloor = \lceil n/p \rceil$. So we need to show:
